@node ee Errors

 It  may  by,  that there exists more than one, and if you tell me about, I
 will fix it. The  only  one  I  know  of is, if you`ll move something in a
 directory/drive, that doesn`t exist, the workbench will tell you this, but
 @{b}Move2.1@{ub} will it move although there. The moved file/directory is now moved
 to Nil:, it will be deleted. In V2.2 this bug will be fixed somehow.
@endnode
@node ue "How To Use"

 The Usage is nearly as easy as the installation. The pattern for @{b}Move V2.1@{ub}
 is:
@{jcenter}
 [from] [to]
@{jleft}
 That means, type @{b}Move2.1@{ub}, space behind and then the source directory,
 space again und then the target directory. Let`s have an example:
@{jcenter}
 @{b}Move2.1@{ub} DF0:Testfile DF1:Testdirectory/Testfile
@{jleft}
 Now would @{b}Move 2.1@{ub} move the file with the name `Testfile` from Drive DF0:
 to Drive DF1: in the directory with the name Testdirectory.
 Important is, that the target file is given, not only the target directory.
 It`s not possible at another way, because of the programing of the copy
 command. But this make it possible to rename the file at the same time you
 move it. Give it simply an new name as source file like this:
@{jcenter}
 @{b}Move2.1@{ub} DF0:Testfile DF1:Testdirectory/TestfileBBCD
@{jleft}
 @{b}Move2.1@{ub} would do now the same like written ahead, only that the file in
 the target directory have the new name TestfileBBCD not Testfile only.
@endnode
@node qe "Quick Starter"
@{jcenter}
Overview to all functions of @{b}Move2.1@{ub} for professional user

Usage:
@{jleft}
  Move [from] [to]
@{jcenter}
Commands:
@{jleft}
  ·h or help - shows a short instruction
  ·? - shows the key for the communication with CLI
  ·nil - deletes file/directory without coping
@endnode
@node ie Installation

 Nothing is easier:  Just copy @{b}Move2.1@{ub} in the C-Directory of your Workbench
 and rename it to @{b}Move@{ub} if you want to.
@endnode
@node we "What Is Move?"

 @{b}Move@{ub}  is  a  batch file, that means it is an executable script, which uses
 only  the  CLI/Shell  standart commands of the workbench, which copies any
 file or a whole directory from the source directory to the destination one
 and deletes the original, like all the other movers do.
 But my @{b}Move@{ub} moves also the icon of the file or directory automatically, if
 one is available. I never found this function in any  other  mover,  exept
 DOpus of course.
 It`s  simply  a  CLI/Shell  command, that combines the copy and the delete
 command. Now you don`t need two steps to work. Just one!
@endnode
